Functions:

int impstr_to_metric(char *impstr, double *mills)


Function description:

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Function        int impstr_to_metric(char *impstr, double *mills)
Description:    Converts a string expressed as a imperial measurement
                and converts it to millimetres.
                
                Valid formats are:

                aa'b-cc/dd
                aa'b~c    
                aa'b.c        

Arguments:      impstr is the string expressed in imperial notation to be converted
                mills is an address to a double to contain the result in 
                millimetres
Returns:        IMPCV_OK  ok
                IMPCV_ERR if impstr is too large to be processed or
                impstr is in an invalid format
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
